==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|forsaken||to reject, deny|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|forsacan||to dispute, quarrel, refuse, oppose|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|farsakanan||to renounce|lang=gem-pro}}, equivalent to {{prefix|for|sake}}. Akin to Middle High German {{term|versachen||to deny|lang=gmh}}, Danish {{term|forsage||to give up|lang=da}}, {{etyl|no|-}} {{term|forsake||to give up, renounce|lang=no}}, Gothic {{term|𐍃𐌰𐌺𐌰𐌽|sc=Goth||tr=sakan||to rebuke, quarrel}}<ref>{{R:Webster 1913|forsake}}</ref>.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/foɻˈseɪk/}}
* {{rhymes|eɪk}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|forsakes|forsaking|forsook|forsaken}}

# To [[abandon]], to give up, to [[leave]] ''([[permanently]])'', to [[renounce]].

